width=\"625\" height=\"220\" alt=\"\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw\" style=\"display:block;object-fit: cover; width: 100%; height: 100%; object-position: 50% 50%\" onload=\"this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)\" srcset=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/60f9881f1e43347bb36172fe/1630588199128-V37JXFTMKHXO2I2DN1S3/Scrum-Chicken-and-Pig.jpg?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/60f9881f1e43347bb36172fe/1630588199128-V37JXFTMKHXO2I2DN1S3/Scrum-Chicken-and-Pig.jpg?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/60f9881f1e43347bb36172fe/1630588199128-V37JXFTMKHXO2I2DN1S3/Scrum-Chicken-and-Pig.jpg?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/60f9881f1e43347bb36172fe/1630588199128-V37JXFTMKHXO2I2DN1S3/Scrum-Chicken-and-Pig.jpg?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/60f9881f1e43347bb36172fe/1630588199128-V37JXFTMKHXO2I2DN1S3/Scrum-Chicken-and-Pig.jpg?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/60f9881f1e43347bb36172fe/1630588199128-V37JXFTMKHXO2I2DN1S3/Scrum-Chicken-and-Pig.jpg?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/60f9881f1e43347bb36172fe/1630588199128-V37JXFTMKHXO2I2DN1S3/Scrum-Chicken-and-Pig.jpg?format=2500w 2500w\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-loader=\"sqs\">\n\n            </div>\n          </div>\n        \n          </a>\n        \n\n        \n      \n        </figure>\n      \n\n    </div>\n  \n\n\n  \n\n\n</div></div><div class=\"sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html\" data-block-type=\"2\" data-border-radii=\"&#123;&quot;topLeft&quot;:&#123;&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;px&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:0.0&#125;,&quot;topRight&quot;:&#123;&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;px&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:0.0&#125;,&quot;bottomLeft&quot;:&#123;&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;px&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:0.0&#125;,&quot;bottomRight&quot;:&#123;&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;px&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:0.0&#125;&#125;\" id=\"block-yui_3_17_2_1_1643659900697_6610\"><div class=\"sqs-block-content\">\n\n<div class=\"sqs-html-content\">\n  <h4 style=\"text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><a href=\"https://subscribe.mvizdos.com\"><strong>SUBSCRIBE FOR FREE TODAY</strong></a></h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n  \n\n\n\n</div></div><div class=\"sqs-block horizontalrule-block sqs-block-horizontalrule\" data-block-type=\"47\" id=\"block-9c83815af39bc706e5bd\"><div class=\"sqs-block-content\"><hr /></div></div><div class=\"sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html\" data-block-type=\"2\" data-border-radii=\"&#123;&quot;topLeft&quot;:&#123;&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;px&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:0.0&#125;,&quot;topRight&quot;:&#123;&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;px&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:0.0&#125;,&quot;bottomLeft&quot;:&#123;&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;px&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:0.0&#125;,&quot;bottomRight&quot;:&#123;&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;px&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:0.0&#125;&#125;\" id=\"block-yui_3_17_2_1_1643648448931_7781\"><div class=\"sqs-block-content\">\n\n<div class=\"sqs-html-content\">\n  <h2 style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\"><strong>The Back Story of the Scrum Chicken and Pig Cartoons</strong></h2><h4 style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">Leap into the Time Machine with me…</h4><h4 style=\"text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;\">2006 (and earlier)</h4><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">The year was 2006.  Fifteen years into my career (and coming off the successful publication of book with <a href=\"https://www.ambysoft.com\" target=\"_blank\">Scott Ambler</a>), I was deep into a full time multi-year consulting engagement with a large financial services firm (that has continued to go through many iterations of Scrum and Agile within their enterprise).  </p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">I had become an “official” Certified Scrum Trainer (by Ken Schwaber as the Scrum Alliance was still pretty much in the beginning stages of moving to a “non-profit” organization).</p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">Ken shared this “Chicken and Pig” story with us back in January of 2004, when I took what was evolving into the “Certified Scrum Master” certification.</p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">At the time, the idea was the <a href=\"https://www.michaelvizdos.com/interactive-scrum-guide#scrum_team\">Scrum Team</a> was made up of “Pigs” (the people doing the work — think <a href=\"https://www.michaelvizdos.com/interactive-scrum-guide#developers\">Developers</a> today)  and “Chickens” (the people who had ideas on how the work would get done — think stakeholders today).  At the time, we were decoupling the idea of a <a href=\"https://www.michaelvizdos.com/interactive-scrum-guide#product_owner\">Product Owner</a> away from being a “Chicken” [which finally happened and they are now an accountability (aka role) on the Scrum Team!].</p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">I was faithfully sharing this story for years, and I asked the community if anyone had drawings of this anywhere (at the time, the agile and scrum world was still pretty small and made up of a bunch of really early adopters lol).   </p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">I got laughed out of the room most of the times I had this conversation about the idea with my peers.</p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">So… seeing an opportunity, I thought I’d get something started.  </p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">One problem.  </p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">I can’t draw.  </p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">So… I put the word out to the community (remember they were telling me this was a dumb idea) and finally found someone (not in the Agile or Scrum Community) who resonated with the idea.  Tony Clark agreed to illustrate the ideas I would come up.  </p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">We published this first comic strip on September 11, 2006 at a new site I created  at <a href=\"/implementing-scrum\">www.ImplementingScrum.com</a>.</p><h4 style=\"text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><strong>Zoom ahead through about 2011</strong></h4><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">Each week, Tony and I bounced ideas off each other.  We would regularly publish a cartoon (illustrated by Tony and concepts co-created by both of us [any errors are mine]).  </p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">An awesome collaboration.</p><p style=\"text-align:right;white-space:pre-wrap;\" class=\"sqsrte-large\"><strong>It kinda took on a life of its own.</strong></p><p style=\"text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;\" class=\"sqsrte-large\">People noticed.  </p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">Heck, the original Scrum cartoon was translated into over a dozen languages (it’s on my <a href=\"https://www.michaelvizdos.com/interactive-scrum-guide#product_backlog\">Product Backlog</a> to publish here again sometime!).</p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">The people who were laughing at the original idea were thinking that it was not such a bad idea anymore.</p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">After publishing over a hundred of these cartoons, we decided to end the series.   </p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">All the content and rights were signed over to me and Tony went on to continue doing incredible things with his life.</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;\">2024 (and beyond)</h3><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">So.  </p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">Here we are.</p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">Calling people “Chickens” and “Pigs” on a Scrum Team is pretty much history.  </p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">Phew.</p><h4 style=\"text-align:right;white-space:pre-wrap;\">For me, the story is still pretty timeless.</h4><p style=\"text-align:right;white-space:pre-wrap;\" class=\"sqsrte-large\">[ … and others, <a href=\"https://kirkdev.blogspot.com/2024/04/the-chicken-and-pig.html\" target=\"_blank\">like this reflection by Kirk Israel</a> ]</p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">Over the past 18+ years, I’ve tried many different iterations of the site and publishing ideas at <a href=\"https://www.implementingscrum.com\">ImplementingScrum.com</a>.</p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">Currently, you can see this original cartoon and learn more about <a href=\"https://start_scrum.mvizdos.com\">starting</a>, <a href=\"https://practice_scrum.mvizdos.com\">practicing</a>, <a href=\"https://coach_scrum.mvizdos.com\">coaching</a>, and <a href=\"https://lead_scrum.mvizdos.com\">leading</a> [not <a href=\"https://manage_scrum.mvizdos.com\">managing</a>] Scrum in the “Real World.”</p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">You know, where you and I live and breathe today :-).</p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">While I am not producing any new cartoons (check out the <a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/*/https://www.implementingscrum.com\" target=\"_blank\">internet way back machine</a> if you are curious), I have kept up the habit of publishing an email every week and sharing a new point of view using one of the original Scrum comic strips. </p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">I’ve done this pretty consistently for 18+ years.  That’s now officially over half of my professional career [eek].</p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">These days, it’s usually an email that I send out to <a href=\"/subscribe\">subscribers</a> on Saturday morning (to thousands of people like you and me).</p><h3 style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">What Next?</h3><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">Meh.  Who knows.</p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">I’ll try and continue the practice of publishing a new <a href=\"https://blog.mvizdos.com\">blog entry</a> on a regular cadence (let’s see if this blog thing is still relevant — I guess if <strong>you</strong> are reading this it’s working!).</p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">I’ll continue sending people one of my Scrum Cartoons with <strong>relevant and timely information about Implementing Scrum</strong> in the real world each weekend.  </p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">It’s OK, you don’t have to read it over the weekend (smile). </p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">I’ll also continue <a href=\"/training\">training</a>, <a href=\"/consulting\">consulting</a>, and <a href=\"/agile-mentoring\">mentoring</a> people around the world.  While it’s been most virtual the past few years, I am starting to do the “in person” travel thing once again [when it’s relatively safe for all of us].</p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">And… </p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">Who knows. </p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">One of <em>your</em> experiences may wind up being shared with others in our growing community of Scrum and Agile people all around the world!</p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\"><a href=\"/contact\">Contact me</a> (with feedback) or <a href=\"https://linkedin.mvizdos.com\" target=\"_blank\">connect with me on LinkedIn</a> to discuss this more together. </p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">Also, check out <a href=\"/agile-mentoring\">AgileMentoring.com</a> while you are here; it’s a great community of practitioners from around the world who are figuring things out together!</p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\"><strong>One final thing…</strong></p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\"><a href=\"/subscribe\">Subscribe</a> to my weekly Saturday morning emails about <a href=\"/implementing-scrum\">Implementing Scrum</a> in the real world.  And get an “every two week” check in from me too.</p><p class=\"sqsrte-large\" style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;\">What could be better?</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n  \n\n\n\n</div></div><div class=\"sqs-block button-block sqs-block-button\" data-block-type=\"53\" id=\"block-2d15e9b14e24adbf9681\"><div class=\"sqs-block-content\">\n\n<div\n  class=\"sqs-block-button-container sqs-block-button-container--center\"\n  data-animation-role=\"button\"\n  data-alignment=\"center\"\n  data-button-size=\"medium\"\n  data-button-type=\"primary\"\n>\n  <a\n    href=\"/subscribe\"\n    class=\"sqs-block-button-element--medium sqs-button-element--primary sqs-block-button-element\"\n    \n  >\n    Subscribe\n  </a>\n</div>\n</div></div></div></div></div></div>\n\n          <div class=\"blog-item-injection\"><hr>\n<h3>\nAbout the Author: Michael Vizdos\n</h3>\n\n<p>Hi. I sincerely appreciate you reading this article. My name is <a href=\"https://www.michaelvizdos.com/about\">Michael Vizdos</a> and I’ve had the privilege of working with thousands of people on teams all around the world over the past 30+ years of my professional career.\n</p>\n<p>\nYou can read more about <a href=\"https://www.michaelvizdos.com/about\">my background</a> or connect with me out on <a href=\"https://linkedin.mvizdos.com\">LinkedIn</a>.\n</p>\n<h4>\nCan you do me a quick favor? \n</h4>\n<p>\nIf you found this article helpful, please \"right click and share\" the following link with your internal team (think slack channels) or out on your favorite social media platform:\n</p>\n \n<p><b><a href=\"https://www.michaelvizdos.com/resources/scrum-chicken-pig-cartoon-origin\">Origin of the Scrum Chicken and Pig Cartoons by Michael Vizdos</a></b>.\n</p>\n\n<p>\n<h4>\nDo you have feedback for me?\n</h4>\n<b><a href=\"https://www.michaelvizdos.com/contact\">Contact me</a></b> and let\'s start a conversation. Really.\n</p>\n\n<p>\nOtherwise... Keep learning more by clicking through the links to my other articles below.  Thank you!\n</p>\n<br>\n<hr></div>\n\n          \n          \n            <div class=\"blog-item-author-profile-wrapper\" data-content-field=\"author\">\n              <a href=\"/resources?author=5ce82bda4152d800018cb468\">\n  \n  <span class=\"author-name\">Michael Vizdos</span>\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"https://www.michaelvizdos.com\" class=\"author-website\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.michaelvizdos.com</a>\n\n            </div>\n          \n        </div>\n\n        <section class=\"blog-item-comments\">\n          <div class=\"blog-item-comments-toggle-wrapper\">\n            <div id=\"blogItemCommentsContent\" class=\"blog-item-comments-content\" data-content-field=\"comments\">\n              \n            </div>\n          </div>\n        </section>\n      \n    </div>\n  \n</article>\n\n</div>\n    </div>\n  \n  </div>\n  \n</section>\n\n  \n</article>\n\n\n          \n\n          \n            \n              <section\n  id=\"itemPagination\"\n  class=\"item-pagination item-pagination--prev-next\"\n  data-collection-type=\"blog-side-by-side\"\n>\n  \n    <a href=\"/resources/scrum-fundamentals\" class=\"item-pagination-link item-pagination-link--prev\">\n      <div class=\"item-pagination-icon icon icon--stroke\">\n        <svg class=\"caret-left-icon--small\" viewBox=\"0 0 9 16\">\n          <polyline fill=\"none\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" points=\"7.3,14.7 2.5,8 7.3,1.2\"/>\n        </svg>\n      </div>\n      <span class=\"pagination-title-wrapper\">\n        \n        <div class=\"visually-hidden\">Previous</div>\n        <div class=\"item-pagination-prev-next\">Previous</div>\n        \n        <h2 class=\"item-pagination-title\">Scrum Fun